Package com.redis.ds.ds_redis.shared

Class RedisKey

java.lang.Object
com.redis.ds.ds_redis.shared.RedisKey
public class RedisKey extends Object
The RedisKey class handles Redis key generation and data object restoration operations. The Redis operations executed via the Jedis programmatic library. You can instantiate this class from the parent RedisDS class. Key Formats: "AppPrefix:Module:RedisType:DataObject:Method:Name[:Id]" (everything except DataItem) "AppPrefix:Module:RedisType:DataObject:Method:Name:DataType:ValueType:ValueFormat" (DataItem) "AppPrefix:Module:RedisType:DataObject:Method:Name:Id:DataType:ValueType:ValueFormat" (DataItem)
Since:
1.0
Author:
Al Cole

    • hashId

      public RedisKey hashId()
      Assigns a hashing id based on a previously assigned data object. Since an object's hash id can change as its members change, you should use another storage mechanism to hold the orignal key name (e.g. you may not be able to derive the same key name from an object if it changed).
      Returns:
      RedisKey instance

    • randomId

      public RedisKey randomId()
      Assigns a random universal unique id. You should only use this method if you plan to track/store your key names in separately.

      RedisKey instance
